data.value:
If for some reason, the comparison between your digest(local), and server digest is not matching. You'll need to contact the rightful provider for help. They have access to their own server and their own database. Kindly have a communication with them so that they can help you upload or edit the correct public key back into their system or database.
This is why recent updates request for your Session's user ID, the provider will contact you via their Session's user ID. However different providers will contact via different means. It's just that in my case, I prefer to use Session user ID as I believe men will have subjective mindset towards certain people, group or even nations. These could be due to political reasons or past or recent events or incidents.
In a similar manner, perhaps it's not new to you that open source authors protested when there's a recent Ukraine and Russia conflict by transforming their projects or libraries into a protestware or in some cases malwares. Specifically aiming to use TOR to mask IP or disguise IP along with identity anonimization is perhaps the most ideal for all. There's perhaps have a higher chance that people don't view each other with subjective point of view and will view each other with objective point of view.
